{"title_page": "Salma Mumin", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name                  = Salma Mumin\n| image                 = \n| imagesize             =\n| alt                   =\n| caption               = \n| birthname             = Salma Mumin\n| birth_date            = \n| birth_plac           = [[Wa, Ghana]], [[Ghana]]\n| othername             =\n| occupation            = Actress and Producer\n| yearsactive           = 2007\u2013present\n| website               =\n}}\n\n'''Salma Mumin''' is a [[Ghanaian]] actress.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/entertainment/Angry-Salma-Mumin-blasts-bloggers-denies-ever-looking-for-a-man-621985|title=Angry Salma Mumin blasts bloggers; denies ever looking for a man|website=www.ghanaweb.com|language=en|access-date=2018-06-05}}</ref> For her work as an actress, she has received several awards and nominations in the movie industry including ''Papyrus Magazine'' Screen Actors Awards (Pamsaa Awards) Best International New Actress in 2014.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.modernghana.com/music/24494/salma-mumin-wins-first-award-after-5-years-of-acting.html|title=Salma Mumin Wins First Award After 5 years of Acting|last=Inusah/Attractive/GhanaState.Com|first=Mustapha A|work=Modern Ghana|access-date=2018-06-05|language=en-gb}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nMumin was born in [[Wa, Ghana|Wa]], in the [[Upper West Region]] of [[Ghana]] and spent her early childhood days there. She attended Odorkor 1 Primary School for her basic education and then moved to Insaaniyya Senior Secondary School.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.celebritiesbuzz.com.gh/actress-salma-mumin-goes-completely-nked-to-celebrate-her-birthday/|title=Actress Salma Mumin goes completely n*ked to celebrate her birthday|last=Bless|first=Papaga|date=2018-12-14|website=CelebritiesBuzz|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref> She later moved to Accra to pursue her acting career.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/entertainment/I-lost-interest-in-school-because-of-acting-Salma-Mumin-410558|title=I lost interest in school because of acting - Salma Mumin|website=www.ghanaweb.com|language=en|access-date=2018-06-05}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nMumin made her screen debut in 2007 where she was featured in the movie ''Passion and Soul''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.graphic.com.gh/entertainment/showbiz-news/salma-produces-no-man-s-land.html|title=Salma produces No Man's Land|last=Duah|first=Kofi|work=Graphic Online|access-date=2018-06-05|language=en-gb}}</ref> Since 2012 she has also played roles in the movies ''Seduction'', ''No Apology'', ''College Girls'', ''Leave my wife'', ''The Will'', ''No Man\u2019s Land'', and ''What My Wife Doesn\u2019t Know'', and ''John and John''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://encomium.ng/fast-rising-ghanaian-actress-salma-mumin-reveals-how-she-fell-in-love-with-acting/|title=Fast rising Ghanaian actress Salma Mumin reveals how she fell in love with acting|work=Encomium Magazine|access-date=2018-06-05|language=en-US}}</ref>  Her first screen performance were in I Love Your Husband 1, 2, and 3 in 2009. she also starred in the film You May Kill the Bride in 20016 .\n\n===Producer===\nIn 2015, she produced her first movie titled ''No Man's Land''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.pulse.com.gh/entertainment/movies/no-man-s-land-everything-you-need-to-know-about-salma-mumin-s-movie-id4662322.html|title=\"No Man's Land\": Everything you need to know about Salma Mumin's movie|last=Mawuli|first=David|access-date=2018-06-05|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Promotional work==\nMumin's face can be seen on [[billboard]]s and TV commercials in Ghana, including commercials for [[uniBank]], Jumbo, Electromart and many more. Her first TV commercial was for [[uniBank]]. She is the brand ambassador for Hollywood Nutritions Slim Smart.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.modernghana.com/entertainment/50103/salma-mumin-is-brand-ambassador-of-hollywood-nutritions-slim.html|title=Salma Mumin Is Brand Ambassador Of Hollywood Nutritions Slim Smart|last=Jeremie|first=Sarah Dankwah|work=Modern Ghana|access-date=2018-06-05|language=en-gb}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{{Div col}}\n*''What My Wife Doesn\u2019t Know''\n*''No Man\u2019s Land'' <ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.peacefmonline.com/pages/showbiz/movies/201602/268831.php|title=Salma Mumin Produces 'No Man's Land'|last=Online|first=Peace FM|access-date=2018-06-05}}</ref>\n*''Seduction''\n*''No Apology''\n*''Passion and Soul''\n*''College Girls''\n*''Leave My Wife''\n*''The Will''\n*''Amakye and Dede''\n*''John and John''\n*''Apples and Bananas''\n{{Div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|id=4449764|name=Salma Mumin}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mumin, Salma}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century Ghanaian actresses]]\n[[Category:Ghanaian film actresses]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name                  = Salma Mumin\n| image                 = \n| imagesize             =\n| alt                   =\n| caption               = \n| birthname             = Salma Mumin\n| birth_date            = \n| birth_plac           = [[Wa, Ghana]], [[Ghana]]\n| othername             =\n| occupation            = Actress and Producer\n| yearsactive           = 2007\u2013present\n| website               =\n}}\n\n'''Salma Mumin''' is a [[Ghanaian]] actress.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/entertainment/Angry-Salma-Mumin-blasts-bloggers-denies-ever-looking-for-a-man-621985|title=Angry Salma Mumin blasts bloggers; denies ever looking for a man|website=www.ghanaweb.com|language=en|access-date=2018-06-05}}</ref> For her work as an actress, she has received several awards and nominations in the movie industry including ''Papyrus Magazine'' Screen Actors Awards (Pamsaa Awards) Best International New Actress in 2014.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.modernghana.com/music/24494/salma-mumin-wins-