a_Mumin"}
{"title_page": "Sir John Mordaunt, 5th Baronet", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=December 2016}}\n'''Sir John Mordaunt, 5th Baronet''' (by 1649 \u2013 6 September 1721) of [[Walton, Warwickshire|Walton d'Eiville]] was an English Tory politician who sat in the [[English House of Commons|English]] and [[House of Commons of Great Britain|British House of Commons]] from 1698 to 1715. \n\nMordaunt was the second son of Sir Charles Mordaunt, 3rd Baronet  and his wife Catherine Tollemache, daughter of [[Sir Lionel Tollemache, 2nd Baronet]], of Helmingham, Suffolk. He succeeded his elder brother to the [[Mordaunt baronets|baronetcy]] on 24 April 1665 and inherited the Massingham Estate at [[Little Massingham]], Norfolk.<ref name=Cokayne1>{{Citation |editor-last=Cokayne |editor-first=George Edward |year=1900 |title= Complete Baronetage volume 1 (1611\u20131625) |url=https://archive.org/stream/cu31924092524374#page/n83/mode/2up |volume=1|location=Exeter |publisher=William Pollard and Co| pages=| accessdate = 9 October 2018 }}</ref> He was one of  Warwickshire's two deputy-lieutenants and following the [[Rye House Plot]]  was involved in organising arms searches  in Warwickshire's main towns in 1683.<ref name=HOP/> He married by licence dated 13 June 1678, aged 21, Anne Risley, daughter of William Risley of the Friary, Bedford. She died in 1692 and he married as his second wife, by licence dated  8 June 1695, Penelope Warburton, the daughter of [[Sir George Warburton, 3rd Baronet]], of Arley, Cheshire.<ref name=Cokayne1/>\n\nMordaunt was returned as [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Warwickshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Warwickshire]] at the [[1698 English general election]]. He held the seat until 1715.<ref name=HOP> {{cite web|url=https://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1690-1715/member/mordaunt-sir-john-1649-1721|title=MORDAUNT, Sir John, 5th Bt. (bef.1649-1721), of Walton D\u2019Eiville, Warws.; Massingham Parva, Norf.; and St. James\u2019s, Westminster, Mdx.|publisher= History of Parliament Trust|accessdate= 19 September 2018}} </ref>\n\nMordaunt died  at Kensington on 6 September 1721.<ref name=Cokayne1/>  He left two sons and two surviving daughters by his second wife, Penelope,  and  was succeeded by his eldest son, [[Sir Charles Mordaunt, 6th Baronet]].<ref name=HOP/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n \n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|en}}\n{{succession box | before=[[William Bromley (speaker)|William Bromley]]<br />[[Andrew Archer (1659\u20131741)|Andrew Archer]] | title=[[Member of Parliament]] for [[Warwickshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Warwickshire]] | with=[[Sir Charles Shuckburgh, 2nd Baronet|Sir Charles Shuckburgh]] 1698\u20131705 | with2=[[Andrew Archer (1659\u20131741)|Andrew Archer]] 1705\u20131707 | years=1698\u20131707 | after=Parliament of Great Britain}}\n{{s-par|gb}}\n{{succession box | before=Parliament of England | title=[[Member of Parliament]] for [[Warwickshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Warwickshire]] | with=[[Andrew Archer (1659\u20131741)|Andrew Archer]] 1707\u20131710, 1713\u20131715 | with2=[[James Compton, 5th Earl of Northampton|Lord Compton]] 1710\u20131712 | with3=[[Sir William Boughton, 4th Baronet|Sir William Boughton]] 1712\u20131713 | years=1707\u20131715 | after=[[Andrew Archer (1659\u20131741)|Andrew Archer]]<br />[[William Peyto (died 1734)|William Peyto]]}}\n{{s-reg|en}}\n{{succession box | before=[[Sir Charles Mordaunt, 4th Baronet|Charles Mordaunt]] | title=[[Mordaunt Baronets|Baronet]]<br />'''(of Massingham Parva)''' | years=1665\u20131721 | after=[[Sir Charles Mordaunt, 6th Baronet|Charles Mordaunt]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mordaunt, John, 5th Baronet}}\n[[Category:Year of birth uncertain]]\n[[Category:17th-century births]]\n[[Category:1721 deaths]]\n[[Category:Baronets in the Baronetage of England]]\n[[Category:English MPs 1698\u20131700]]\n[[Category:English MPs 1701]]\n[[Category:English MPs 1701\u20131702]]\n[[Category:English MPs 1702\u20131705]]\n[[Category:English MPs 1705\u20131707]]\n[[Category:Members of the Parliament of Great Britain for English constituencies]]\n[[Category:British MPs 1707\u20131708]]\n[[Category:British MPs 1708\u20131710]]\n[[Category:British MPs 1710\u20131713]]\n[[Category:British MPs 1713\u20131715]]\n\n{{Baronet-stub}}\n{{England-pre1707-MP-stub}}\n{{England-GreatBritain-MP-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=December 2016}}\n'''Sir John Mordaunt, 5th Baronet''' (by 1649 \u2013 6 September 1721) of [[Walton, Warwickshire|Walton d'Eiville]] was an English Tory politician who sat in the [[English House of Commons|English]] and [[House of Commons of Great Britain|British House of Commons]] from 1698 to 1715. \n\nMordaunt was the second son of Sir Charles Mordaunt, 3rd Baronet  and his wife Catherine Tollemache, daughter of Sir Lionel Tollemache, 2nd Baronet, of Helmingham, Suffolk. He succeeded his elder brother to the [[Mordaunt baronets|baronetcy]] on 24 April 1665 and inherited the Massingham Estate at [[Little Massingham]], Norfolk.<ref name=Cokayne1>{{Citation |editor-last=Cokayne |editor-first=George Edward |year=1900 |title= Complete Baronetage volume 1 (1611\u20131625) |url=https://archive.org/stream/cu31924092524374#page/n83/mode/2up |volume=1|location=Exeter |publisher=William Pollard and Co| pages=| accessdate = 9 October 2018 }}</ref> He was one of  Warwickshire's two deputy-lieutenants and following the [[Rye House Plot]]  was involved in organising arms searches  in Warwickshire's main towns in 1683.<ref name=HOP/> He married by licence dated 13 June 1678, aged 21, Anne Risley, daughter of William Risley of the Friary, Bedford. She died in 1692 and he married as his second wife, by licence dated  8 June 1695, Penelope Warburton, the daughter of [[Sir George Warburton, 3rd Baronet]], of Arley, Cheshire.<ref name=Cokayne1/>\n\nMordaunt was returned as [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Warwickshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Warwickshire]] at the [[1698 English general election]]. He held the seat until 1715.<ref name=HOP> {{cite web|url=https://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1690-1715/member/mordaunt-sir-john-1649-1721|title=MORDAUNT, Sir John, 5th Bt. (bef.1649-1721), of Walton D\u2019Eiville, Warws.; Massingham Parva, Norf.; and St. James\u2019s, Westminster, Mdx.|publisher= History of Parliament Trust|accessdate= 19 September 2018}} </ref>\n\nMordaunt died  at Kensington on 6 September 1721.<ref name=Cokayne1/>  He left two sons and two surviving daughters by his second wife, Penelope,  and  was succeeded by his eldest son, [[Sir Charles Mordaunt, 6th Baronet]].<ref name=HOP/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n \n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|en}}\n{{succession box | before=[[William Bromley (speaker)|William Bromley]]<br />[[Andrew Archer (1659\u20131741)|Andrew Archer]] | title=[[Member of Parliament]] for [[Warwickshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Warwickshire]] | with=[[Sir Charles Shuckburgh, 2nd Baronet|Sir Charles Shuckburgh]] 1698\u20131705 | with2=[[Andrew Archer (1659\u20131741)|Andrew Archer]] 1705\u20131707 | years=1698\u20131707 | after=Parliament of Great Britain}}\n{{s-par|gb}}\n{{succession box | before=Parliament of England | title=[[Member of Parliament]] for [[Warwickshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Warwickshire]] | with=[[Andrew Archer (1659\u20131741)|Andrew Archer]] 1707\u20131710, 1713\u20131715 | with2=[[James Compton, 5th Earl of Northampton|Lord Compton]] 1710\u20131712 | with3=[[Sir William Boughton, 4th Baronet|Sir William Boughton]] 1712\u20131713 | years=1707\u20131715 | after=[[Andrew Archer (1659\u20131741)|Andrew Archer]]<br />[[William Peyto (died 1734)|William Peyto]]}}\n{{s-reg|en}}\n{{succession box | before=[[Sir Charles Mordaunt, 4th Baronet|Charles Mordaunt]] | title=[[Mordaunt Baronets|Baronet]]<br />'''(of Massingham Parva)''' | years=1665\u20131721 | after=[[Sir Charles Mordaunt, 6th Baronet|Charles Mordaunt]]}}