\n* '''[[Achaea Football Clubs Association|Achaea FCA]] Cup'''\n** '''Winners (4):''' 1936-37, 1993-94, 2006-07, 2008-09\n* '''[[Achaea Football Clubs Association|Achaea FCA]] Super Cup'''\n** '''Winners (1):''' 2007\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.panaigialeios1927.gr/ Official website]\n\n{{Panegialios F.C.}}\n{{Navboxes|title = Panegialios F.C. templates|titlestyle = background:white; color:black; {{box-shadow border|a|black|1px}}\n|list1=\n{{Panegialios F.C. squad}}\n{{Panegialios F.C. managers}}\n}}\n{{Football League 2 (Greece)}}\n{{Superleague Greece teamlist}}\n\n[[Category:Panegialios F.C.| ]]\n[[Category:Aigio]]\n[[Category:Association football clubs established in 1927]]\n[[Category:Football clubs in Western Greece]]\n[[Category:1927 establishments in Greece]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football club |\n clubname = Panegialios|\n image    = Panegialios.jpg|\n fullname = Panegialios Gymnastics Club|\n nickname = ''\u039c\u03b1\u03cd\u03c1\u03b7 \u0398\u03cd\u03b5\u03bb\u03bb\u03b1'' (Black Storm) <br />''\u03a0\u03b1\u03c3\u03ac\u03b4\u03b5\u03c2 \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u0391\u03b9\u03b3\u03af\u03bf\u03c5'' (Pasades of Aigio)|\n founded  = {{Start date and years ago|df=yes|1927|2|25}}|\n ground   = Aigio National Stadium  |\n capacity = 7,000|\n  season = [[2017\u201318 Football League (Greece)|2017\u201318]]|\n chairman = Dimitris Balafoutis|\n manager  = Christos Karapitsos|\n  league = [[Gamma Ethniki]]\n|\n  position = [[Football League (Greece)|Football League]], 15th (relegated)\n\n| website  = http://www.panaigialeios1927.gr/ |\n pattern_la1=__black_stripes|pattern_b1=_juve1011h|pattern_ra1=__black_stripes| pattern_sh1 =_nikewhite|| pattern_so1 =_nikewhite|\n leftarm1=ffffff|body1=|rightarm1=ffffff|shorts1=000000|socks1=000000|\n pattern_la2=__trim|pattern_b2=_peter1112a|pattern_ra2=__trim| pattern_sh2 =_nikewhite|pattern_so2 =_nikeblack|\n leftarm2=ffffff|body2=ffffff|rightarm2=ffffff|shorts2=000000|socks2=ffffff|\n|pattern_b3=_psg1011t|pattern_ra3=_black_hoops|pattern_la3=_black_hoops\n| pattern_sh3 =_nikewhite |pattern_so3=_nikeblack\n| leftarm3    = |body3=800000|rightarm3=|lefttarm3=800000|shorts3=000000|socks3=FFFFFF\n| current  = 2017\u201318 Panegialios F.C. season\n}}\n\n'''Panegialios''' ({{lang-el|\u03a0\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03b9\u03b3\u03b9\u03ac\u03bb\u03b5\u03b9\u03bf\u03c2 \u0393.\u03a3.}} (''Panegialios Gymnastics Club'', referring to [[Aigialeia]], a subprefecture covering the northeastern part of [[Achaea]]) is a [[Association football|football]] club based in [[Aigio]], [[Greece]]. Panaigialios has a long tradition in Greek football championships and has several appearances in the Greek Super League (former A' Ethniki), 2nd Division and 3rd Division. Additionally the team has reached twice the semi-finals of the Greek Cup competition. Panegialios is one of the most successful and popular teams in Achaea and [[Peloponnese]].\n\n==History==\nThe club was founded on 25 February 1927 in Egio by local selected community members. The man who inspired the idea of the formation of a football club in Egio was Zisimos Livas. Livas, a well-known architect, together with Nick Gardeniotis, C. Sakellaropoulos, Ir. Anastasopoulos, K. Eliopoulos, K. Liritzis, Chr. Papandianos, etc. have established Panegialios G.S. It is worth to mention that the effort for the formation of a football club in Egio had begun from Livas in 1924. Until 1927 Livas and the other co-founders have raised money in order to establish the club. Finally in February 1927 they submitted the statute foundation of the club to the local judicial authorities.\n\n=== Nicknames ===\nPanegialios nickname since the late-1950s was Mavri Thiella (Black Storm). Also his players called Pasades tou Aigiou because they were very well paid for that era.\n\n=== Greek cup ===\nPanegialios has a big tradition in Greek Cup and twice reached the semi finals, in 1959 and 1981. Both has lost the qualification in the final from Olympiacos Piraeus. Additionally the club has reached the quarter finals twice.\n\n==Crest and colours==\nLike most old football clubs, Panegialios did not initially have any badge displayed on their shirts. The club's crest depicts two wrestlers of Greco-Roman wrestling. It is quite unusual for a football club to have a crest that refers to wrestling but the explanation has to do with Panegialios founder, Zisimos Livas. Livas was a lover Greco-Roman wrestling and had been an athlete of wrestling in [[Panellinios G.S]]. So in 1954 after the death of Zisimos Livas, the President of the Club Sotirios Panagiotopoulos in order to honor him, has decided to adopt the club the two wrestlers as a crest.\nThe colours of the team are black and white since 1927.\n\n==Stadium==\nPanegialios home ground is Aeghio Municipal (formerly \"National\") Stadium which has two stands along the sides of the pitch. The stadium has two almost identical stands, with electronic projectors, a modern canteen as well as a caf\u00e9. The stadium was inaugurated on April 29, 1949. In this location the stadium was formerly a football stadium, with no stands and surrounding arenas and other infrastructure, which was the seat of Panegyalos since its foundation in 1927. In 1983, it was placed on turf and 2011 plastic coating on the arena that surrounds the pitch of the football field. The stadium also had two similar small petals that raised the capacity of over 11,000 spectators. The petals were demolished during its refurbishment in 1985 except for a small section double of the western platform.\n\nThe record at the stage was 1963 in a match for the First National Division ([[Alpha Ethniki]]), between Panegialios and [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]], with 14,119 spectators.\n\n==Supporters==\nPanegialios F.C. has always had loyal supporters. The first fan club was created during the 1970s. It was called Sindesmos Filathlon Aigiou (S.F.A.) and later changed in Sindesmos Filathlon Panaigialeiou. In 2006 Bianconeri Club has established with strong presence in Panaigialios matches until nowadays.\n\n==League divisions==\n===League appearances ===\nPanegialos league appearances in national divisions since 1958-59. It is one of the few clubs that has participated in all four national Greek divisions.\n* [[Alpha Ethniki]] - 7 appearances\n* [[Football League (Greece)|Beta Ethniki]] - 21 appearances \n* [[Football League 2 (Greece)|Gamma Ethniki]] - 15 appearances \n* [[Delta Ethniki]] - 15 appearances\n\n===National===\n*[[Gamma Ethniki 2012-13|2012-13]]: [[Gamma Ethniki|Gamma Ethniki (Third division)]] (South Group) 1st\n*[[Football League (Greece) 2013-14|2013-14]]: [[Football League (Greece)|Football League]] (South Group): 5th\n*[[Football League (Greece) 2014-15|2014-15]]: [[Football League (Greece)|Football League]] (South Group): 6th\n*[[Football League (Greece) 2015-16|2015-16]]: [[Football League (Greece)|Football League]]: 12th\n*[[Football League (Greece) 2016-17|2016-17]]: [[Football League (Greece)|Football League]]:  8th\n*[[Football League (Greece) 2017-18|2017-18]]: [[Football League (Greece)|Football League]]: 16th\n*[[Gamma Ethniki 2018-19|2018-19]]: [[Gamma Ethniki|Gamma Ethniki (Third division)]] 12th\n\n==Players==\n===Current squad===\n{{updated|16 October 2018}}\n{{Fs start}}\n{{Fs player| no= | nat=GRE | pos=GK | name=[[Panagiotis Dounis]]}}\n{{Fs player| no= | nat=GRE | pos=GK | name=George Panagiotopoulos}}\n{{Fs player| no= | nat=GRE | pos=GK | name=Dimitris Mouzos}}\n----\n{{Fs player| no= | nat=GRE | pos=DF | name=Marios Tzanoulinos }}\n{{Fs player| no= | nat=GRE | pos=DF | name=Giannis Gramatikas}}\n{{Fs player| no= | nat=GRE | pos=DF | name=Stavros Christodoulopoulos}}\n{{Fs player| no= | nat=GRE | pos=DF | name=Dimitris Kyriakopoulos}}\n{{Fs player| no= | nat=GRE | pos=DF | name=Lefteris Mero }}\n{{Fs player| no= | nat=ALB| pos=DF | name=Erion Aintin }}\n{{Fs player| no= | nat=ALB| pos=DF | name=Armirad Kola }}\n{{Fs player| no= | nat=GRE|